* Represents a function that accepts a long-valued argument and produces a * result. This is the {@code long}-consuming primitive specialization for * {@link Function}. * *

This is a functional interface * whose functional method is {@link #apply(long)}. * * @param the type of the result of the function * * @see Function * @since 1.8

methods.name: R apply(long value)

* Applies this function to the given argument.
     *
     * @param value the function argument
     * @return the function result
